---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Strategies | Cutler Capital Management">
  <body>
    <main id="main">
      <section class="page-hero">
        <div class="container">
          <p class="eyebrow">Investment Strategies</p>
          <h1>Portfolios from aggressive to defensive, built with a repeatable process.</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            Our portfolios span a range of risk profiles while allowing for customization around diversification, liquidity, and other client circumstances.
            We revise portfolios over time as conditions change, and we stay engaged to ensure the portfolio continues to reflect your goals.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-head">
            <h2>Portfolio profiles</h2>
            <p class="muted">Three profiles provide a simple starting point. Portfolio construction and implementation can be customized.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="grid-3">
            <div class="card">
              <h3>Aggressive</h3>
              <p class="muted">Seeks equity-like long-term returns, with risk awareness.</p>
              <ul class="person-bullets">
                <li>Typically oriented toward convertibles and dividend-paying equities</li>
                <li>Often includes community banks and REITs</li>
                <li>Designed for higher growth objectives and longer horizons</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <h3>Balanced</h3>
              <p class="muted">Targets a profile comparable to a classic 60/40 mix, with less risk.</p>
              <ul class="person-bullets">
                <li>Convertibles as a core allocation</li>
                <li>Dividend-paying equities (including community banks and REITs)</li>
                <li>Emphasis on diversification and risk controls</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <h3>Conservative</h3>
              <p class="muted">Seeks income and downside protection with potential for growth.</p>
              <ul class="person-bullets">
                <li>Heavily weighted toward convertible securities</li>
                <li>May include selected dividend-paying equities</li>
                <li>Structured to reduce the likelihood of permanent loss</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-alt">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-head">
            <h2>How portfolios are constructed</h2>
            <p class="muted">
              Each strategy is anchored by a disciplined portfolio management process: quantitative screening, followed by detailed credit and
              fundamental analysis, and then portfolio construction based on relative value and risk attributes.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="grid-3">
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>Screen</h3>
              <p>We begin with quantitative screening to narrow the opportunity set in a consistent, repeatable way.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>Underwrite</h3>
              <p>We then perform detailed credit and fundamental analysis, focusing on downside and valuation support.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="feature">
              <h3>Construct</h3>
              <p>We build portfolios of convertibles, bonds, and equities based on relative value and risk attributes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="callout">
            <div class="callout-inner">
              <div>
                <h3 class="callout-title">A structural differentiator: convertible securities</h3>
                <p class="muted">
                  Across our portfolio profiles, convertibles are a consistent building block. They are hybrid securities that combine features of
                  equity and debt, with the potential to participate in rising equity markets while offering downside protection when equity prices
                  are flat or declining.
                </p>
              </div>
              <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/philosophy/">Read the philosophy</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Focus Areas (3 tiles -> jump to 3 on-page sections) -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-head">
            <h2>Focus areas</h2>
            <p class="muted">We concentrate on areas where specialization and sustained research effort can matter.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="grid-3 focus-tiles">
            <a class="tile tile-link" href="/focus/banks/">
              <h3>Community Banks</h3>
              <p class="muted">
                An under-researched segment where bank-by-bank underwriting, asset quality work, and cycle discipline can create an edge.
                We tend to focus on community banks seeking to grow their footprint.
              </p>
              <p class="small muted">Sector investing involves risk, including credit, liquidity, and regulatory risks.</p>
              <span class="tile-cta">View research →</span>
            </a>

            <a class="tile tile-link" href="/focus/convertibles/">
              <h3>Convertible Securities</h3>
              <p class="muted">
                Convertibles combine interest payments with the option to receive shares instead of cash at repayment. This structure can offer
                equity upside participation with meaningful downside characteristics.
              </p>
              <p class="small muted">Convertible prices are influenced by interest rates, issuer credit, and the underlying equity.</p>
              <span class="tile-cta">View framework →</span>
            </a>

            <a class="tile tile-link" href="/focus/reits/">
              <h3>REITs</h3>
              <p class="muted">
                REITs can provide income and diversification across real asset categories. Historically, REITs have offered downside characteristics
                with upside potential, and can play a role as a portfolio diversifier.
              </p>
              <p class="small muted">REITs are sensitive to economic cycles and can be volatile.</p>
              <span class="tile-cta">View approach →</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <style>
      /* Make tiles behave like links without changing your global tile styling */
      .focus-tiles .tile-link {
        display: block;
        text-decoration: none;
        color: inherit;
      }
      .focus-tiles .tile-link:hover .tile-cta {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }
      .tile-cta {
        display: inline-block;
        margin-top: 0.75rem;
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      /* Give these charts a “real” surface feel (works with your existing placeholder layout) */
      .chart-surface .chart-placeholder__inner.chart-inner {
        padding: 1.1rem;
      }
      .chart-surface {
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
      }

      /* ---------- Animated Community Bank Lifecycle (CSS-only) ---------- */
      .lifecycle {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
        gap: 1.25rem;
        align-items: center;
        min-height: 320px;
      }

      .lifecycle-ring {
        position: relative;
        width: 200px;
        height: 200px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.14);
        background:
          radial-gradient(circle at 30% 25%, rgba(255,255,255,0.55), transparent 55%),
          linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(124,25,45,0.14), rgba(124,25,45,0.04));
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      /* A rotating sweep to imply “cycle” */
      .lifecycle-ring::before {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        inset: -50%;
        background: conic-gradient(
          from 0deg,
          rgba(124,25,45,0.0),
          rgba(124,25,45,0.35),
          rgba(124,25,45,0.0)
        );
        animation: spin 6s linear infinite;
      }

      .lifecycle-ring::after {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        inset: 12px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
        border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.10);
      }

      .lifecycle-dot {
        position: absolute;
        width: 12px;
        height: 12px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        background: #7c192d;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.18);
        z-index: 2;
        animation: dotPulse 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;
      }
      .lifecycle-dot:nth-child(1) { top: 10px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); }
      .lifecycle-dot:nth-child(2) { right: 10px; top: 50%; transform: translateY(-50%); animation-delay: .3s; }
      .lifecycle-dot:nth-child(3) { bottom: 10px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); animation-delay: .6s; }
      .lifecycle-dot:nth-child(4) { left: 10px; top: 50%; transform: translateY(-50%); animation-delay: .9s; }

      .lifecycle-steps {
        display: grid;
        gap: 0.75rem;
      }

      .lstep {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 34px 1fr;
        gap: 0.75rem;
        align-items: start;
        padding: 0.75rem 0.85rem;
        border-radius: 14px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.10);
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
      }

      .lstep-kicker {
        width: 34px;
        height: 34px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        display: grid;
        place-items: center;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #fff;
        background: #7c192d;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.16);
      }

      .lstep-title {
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.2;
      }

      .lstep-sub {
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        margin-top: 0.15rem;
      }

      .lifecycle-caption {
        grid-column: 1 / -1;
        margin-top: 0.35rem;
      }

      @keyframes spin {
        to { transform: rotate(360deg); }
      }
      @keyframes dotPulse {
        0%, 100% { transform: translateX(-50%) scale(1); opacity: 0.9; }
        50% { transform: translateX(-50%) scale(1.25); opacity: 1; }
      }

      /* Fix transform overrides for dot positions */
      .lifecycle-dot:nth-child(2),
      .lifecycle-dot:nth-child(4) {
        animation-name: dotPulseY;
      }
      @keyframes dotPulseY {
        0%, 100% { transform: translateY(-50%) scale(1); opacity: 0.9; }
        50% { transform: translateY(-50%) scale(1.25); opacity: 1; }
      }

      /* Responsive: stack lifecycle on small screens */
      @media (max-width: 880px) {
        .lifecycle {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
        .lifecycle-ring {
          margin: 0 auto;
        }
      }

      /* ---------- Animated Bars (CSS-only) ---------- */
      .bars-head {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
        margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
      }

      .bars {
        display: grid;
        grid-auto-flow: column;
        grid-auto-columns: minmax(10px, 1fr);
        gap: 10px;
        align-items: end;
        height: 260px;
        padding: 0.5rem 0.25rem 0.25rem;
        border-radius: 14px;
        border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.10);
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
        overflow-x: auto;
        overscroll-behavior-x: contain;
        scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
      }

      .bar {
        position: relative;
        width: 18px;
        min-width: 18px;
        border-radius: 10px 10px 6px 6px;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(124,25,45,0.92), rgba(124,25,45,0.55));
        height: calc((var(--v) / var(--max)) * 100%);
        animation: grow 900ms ease-out both;
        transform-origin: bottom;
        scroll-snap-align: end;
      }

      .bar::after {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        inset: 1px 1px auto 1px;
        height: 55%;
        border-radius: 9px 9px 6px 6px;
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.10);
      }

      .bar-year,
      .bar-val {
        position: absolute;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translateX(-50%);
        white-space: nowrap;
        font-size: 10px;
        color: rgba(0,0,0,0.70);
      }

      .bar-year {
        bottom: -18px;
      }

      .bar-val {
        top: -16px;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: rgba(0,0,0,0.78);
      }

      @keyframes grow {
        from { transform: scaleY(0.05); opacity: 0.35; }
        to { transform: scaleY(1); opacity: 1; }
      }

      .bars-foot {
        margin-top: 0.75rem;
      }

      @media (max-width: 620px) {
        .bar { width: 14px; min-width: 14px; }
        .bars { gap: 8px; height: 230px; }
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</BaseLayout>
